# Matthew Fredrick
**Senior AI/ML Software Engineer**
Chelmsford, MA | mcfredrick@pm.me | linkedin.com/in/mattcfredrick | github.com/mcfredrick
---
## Key Achievements
- **Enterprise AI Safety at Scale** – Designed and shipped LLM guardrails and safety features protecting millions of users across Cisco's collaboration platforms; deployed models spanning content filtering, prompt injection defense, jailbreak prevention, and toxicity detection

- **End-to-End ML System Ownership** – Led initiatives from conception to production, including synthetic data pipelines that reduced data-creation effort by ~90%, autonomous red-teaming agents, and multilingual safety classifiers across multiple classification domains

- **MLOps Platform Architecture** – Architected a comprehensive MLOps platform for AI/ML model lifecycle management using Airflow and MLflow; established organizational standards for continuous training, monitoring, and deployment adopted across multiple teams
- **Rapid Iteration & Model Improvement** – Identified and resolved mis-categorized edge cases in security models, directly improving customer protection; designed fine-tuning workflows that reduced issue resolution from days to minutes

- **Cross-Functional Technical Leadership** – Partner daily with product, security, linguistics, and platform teams to align technical solutions with business goals; go-to technical authority for MLOps strategy across the organization
- **Mentorship & Talent Development** – Mentor colleagues through formal programs; mentees have advanced to new roles, owned major features end-to-end, and are driving positive change on their teams
---
## Technical Skills

**ML/AI**: PyTorch, TensorFlow, scikit-learn, Hugging Face Transformers, custom classification models, computer vision, transformer fine-tuning, AI agents, guardrails development, synthetic data generation
**ML Operations**: Weights & Biases, MLflow, Airflow, GitHub Actions, CI/CD pipelines, A/B testing, model evaluation frameworks
**Cloud & Infrastructure**: AWS, Azure, Kubernetes, Pulumi, Docker, Infrastructure-as-Code
**Programming**: Python, C++, Rust

**Tools & Platforms**: Git, Grafana, Windsurf, Claude Code
**AI-Assisted Development**: Developing and contributing best practices and reusable workflows for AI coding assistants (Claude Code, Codex) to team knowledgebase, enabling engineers across the org to ship faster while maintaining high code quality through rigorous human review
---
## Professional Experience
### **Senior Software Engineer - AI Platform** | Cisco (Collaboration AI/Webex) | June 2022 – Present

- **MLOps Platform** – Architected modular, reusable infrastructure patterns for AI/ML model lifecycle management; established organizational standards for continuous training, monitoring, and deployment; became the go-to technical authority for MLOps strategy
- **Synthetic Data Pipeline** – Designed and shipped modular system that cut data-creation effort by ~90%; extended to support multilingual expansion and multiple classification domains (toxicity, harm detection); new training sets generated in minutes

- **AI Security Model Improvements** – Delivered measurable improvements to security classifiers by identifying mis-categorized edge cases; pioneered synthetic data generation pipeline enabling continuous fine-tuning and data-driven model evaluation
- **Automated Testing Framework** – Built comprehensive testing framework for AI agent validation including objective generation, notification capabilities, and system tests for full coverage

- **ML-Ops & Continuous Metrics** – Engineered CI/CD pipelines pushing performance data to Weights & Biases for real-time visibility; 49 PRs merged across 15 repositories in 12 months
- **Business-Metric Instrumentation** – Conceived and delivered lightweight library standardizing metric collection across 8+ microservices; produces per-user cost dashboards in Grafana backed by S3 storage

- **Multilingual Model PoC** – Led development with linguistics partners, extending language support for LLM guardrails security service
- **Document Ingestion for RAG** – Architected OCR + parsing pipeline as a hosted service, taking it from POC to production; enables retrieval-augmented generation workflows

- **AI-Enhanced Video Pipelines** – Built computer vision pipelines delivering smooth, low-latency video enhancements for millions worldwide; optimized background blur, virtual backgrounds, and relighting for efficient performance on diverse hardware
- **Cross-Functional Leadership** – Daily partnership with product, platform, linguistics, and security teams; regular briefings to senior leadership; led knowledge transfer across teams through internal presentations

### **Software Developer** | BandLab Technologies | November 2019 – April 2022
- Owned audio software features from design to delivery for a global music-creation platform, collaborating closely across engineering, product, and design teams
- Built cross-platform applications using C++, JUCE framework, and audio plugin SDKs (VST/AU), ensuring seamless integration and user experience
- Designed, implemented, and debugged systems spanning GUI, DSP, user data persistence, and cloud integration

- Maintained high code quality standards and collaborated effectively in a distributed team environment
### **Software Engineering Consultant** | DayJobDevelopment LLC | June 2019 – Present
- Audio and music technology consulting focusing on AI/ML audio manipulation and music information retrieval, C++, JUCE, Python, DSP, and web technologies
- Delivered custom software solutions for clients across diverse technical domains

### **Inventor Drafting/Automation Specialist** | Ipswich Bay Glass | February 2018 – July 2018
- Automated drafting workflows and data handling in Autodesk Inventor using C++ and VBA
- Reduced time to production through custom software solutions integrating with CAD/CAM systems
### **Design Engineer** | SARC Inc | October 2017 – January 2018
- Owned R&D projects from conception to production with strong focus on documentation and version control

- Leveraged prototypes and technical communication to drive stakeholder engagement
### **Solutions Engineer** | Vacuum Technology, Inc. | October 2014 – September 2015
- Delivered customized technical solutions to researchers in private and government laboratories
- Created new documentation standards and provided remote/in-person technical training
